Description: Unique identifier for the digital or intellectual property asset.
Type of digital or IP asset (e.g., 'Patent', 'Copyright', 'Trademark', 'Domain', 'NFT', 'Crypto', 'Social Media Account').
Name or title of the asset.
Name of the individual or entity who owns the asset.
Governing body or platform where the asset is registered (e.g., USPTO, Ethereum, GoDaddy, Twitter).
Registration or unique asset ID (if applicable).
Date of expiration or renewal (if applicable).
Method used to determine value (e.g., market, appraised, floor price).
Indicates if the asset is transferable or sellable (Y/N).
Associated wallet address or account handle (e.g., Twitter handle, ETH wallet).
Location of credentials (e.g., password manager, custodian).
Indicates if digital documentation or proof exists (Y/N).
Link to legal or ownership documentation.
Timestamp of the last metadata update.
